<TITLE> Iran arrests senior political party figure </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 TEHRAN, May 18 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Iranian authorities have arrested a senior member of a political party for "security crimes", Sharq newspaper reported on Tuesday. Iran's government is wary of protests erupting on the anniversary of elections last June that led to unprecedented protests by opponents of President Mahmoud Ahmadinejad who claimed the vote was rigged. "Mohsen Armin a member of the Mujahideen of Islamic Revolution party was arrested on the charges of committing security crimes," Sharq quoted Tehran prosecutor Abbas Jafari Dolatabadi as saying. "His file is now in court and the investigations are underway," it said. The paper quoted his daughter as saying security officers came to their house with an arrest warrant and searched the premises. Iranian authorities tried to arrest Armin, a senior member of the party, just after last year's elections and after rioting in December but he was away from home on both occasions. Five members of a Kurdish group viewed as "anti-revolutionary" were hanged this month. Opposition leader Mirhossein Mousavi attacked the executions as an effort to warn people way from renewing protes
